messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /api/user

- All methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: true
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In main() hello.go, routes are grouped under v1 := r.Group("/api"). The user-specific routes are registered with users.UserRegister(v1.Group("/user")), so the group's base path is /api/user.
- In users/routers.go, UserRegister registers router.GET("/", UserRetrieve) and router.PUT("/", UserUpdate). Those are the only handlers attached to this group path, so the endpoint implemented by UserRetrieve corresponds to GET on /api/user (the GET is registered on the group's "/" so combined: /api + /user + / = /api/user).
- There is no router.Any or similar that would allow all HTTP methods, so "All methods acceptable" is false.
- Only GET and PUT are explicitly registered for this path in the code; per the instructions we do not assume implicit framework behavior (e.g., automatic HEAD handling), so HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, DELETE, PATCH are false.
